  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;All new external facing and roofing materials in respect of all the works hereby approved (and any other incidental works carried out in this connection) shall match those of the existing building in respect of materials used, detailed execution and finished appearance unless otherwise shown on the hereby approved plans.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\nREASON: In the interesting of preserving and maintaining the character and appearance of the host building and conservation area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "Prior to the commencement of the relevant part of the work, details of the hereby approved biodiverse roof shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, details shall include a detailed layout, cross sections (scale 1:20), full specifications and a detailed management and maintenance plan of the biodiverse roof with a minimum substrate depth of 80mm, not including the vegetative mat. The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved and shall be fully implemented before the first use of the approved development.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;REASON: In the interest of enhancing biodiversity and to provide a suitable sustainable urban drainage system on site.&amp;nbsp;"
  ],
